    <text>
        <body>
             <div type="edition" subtype="ogham" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" resp="#POC">              
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-top-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">ᚁᚔᚏ</name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">ᚋᚐᚊᚔ</w> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">ᚋᚒᚉᚑᚔ</w> <name nymRef="#?">ᚏᚑᚈᚈᚐᚔᚄ</name></persName>
                </ab> 
            </div>                    
            <div type="edition" subtype="transliteration" xml:lang="pgl-Ogam" xml:space="preserve" resp="#POC">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1" style="text-direction:up-top-down"/><persName><name nymRef="#?">BIR</name> <w type="formula" lemma="maqqas">MAQI</w> <w type="formula" lemma="muccoviias">MUCOI</w> <name nymRef="#?">ROTTAIS</name></persName>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                <app n="1">
            <note>The inscription likely follows the formula X son and descendent of Y.</note>                    
                </app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>Berr (the short-haired one) son of and belonging to the family of Rothrige</p> <!-- Check this!-->
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                 <p>The modern form of the first personal name, BIR, is <persName xml:lang="ga"><ref target="https://dil.ie/5721">Berr</ref></persName> 'short-haired' (McManus 1991, 106). The final word in the inscription, ROTTAIS, might be a reference to the tribal name <persName xml:lang="sga">Rothrige</persName> (McManus 1991, 111, 180 n60) which is listed amongst the subject communities of the <distinct xml:lang="ga">Déisi</distinct> of Munster.</p>
            </div>
